          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the Egypt Golden Visa program established?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            The program launched in 2024, making it relatively new. Implementation is ongoing,
            and processes may evolve. Work with an experienced immigration lawyer who tracks
            current requirements and procedures.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I work in Egypt with the Golden Visa?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Yes, Golden Visa holders can work and conduct business in Egypt. For company
            investment route, you're expected to actively manage your business. Real estate
            and bank deposit routes allow freedom to work or not as you choose.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How safe is property investment in Egypt?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Property in established areas of Cairo is generally safe. New cities (New Administrative
            Capital, New Alamein) carry more development risk. Always verify developer track records,
            use established lawyers, and consider escrow for off-plan purchases.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Egypt's currency risk manageable?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            The Egyptian Pound has devalued significantly against the dollar. For dollar-based
            investors, this means cheaper living costs but currency conversion losses on
            Egyptian-denominated assets. Maintain savings in hard currency and plan accordingly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can my family join me on the Golden Visa?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Yes, your spouse and dependent children can be included in your application.
            Each family member receives a residence card valid for the same duration as
            the principal applicant.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does taxation work for Golden Visa holders?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
            Egypt taxes residents on worldwide income after 183 days of presence. Tax rates
            are progressive up to 25%. However, many income sources may be covered by double
            taxation treaties. Consult a tax professional for your specific situation.
          </p>
        </div>
